- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Distance: 80 kilometers from HCMC</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cost: VND1-2 million ($40 to $82)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Budget-friendly getaways near HCMC for National Day holidays', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '19-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-08-30 08:39:34', '2023-08-30 08:39:34', '', 19, 'http://localhost:8888/trang/?p=21', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(22, 1, '2023-08-30 08:41:28', '2023-08-30 08:41:28', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The amount of calories in durians is several times higher than that in other fruits. Is it too much if I have five durian pulps every day? (Nhu, 27, HCMC)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Answer:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Durians have several benefits to health. They contain an amino acid called tryptophan which helps produce serotonin, a neurotransmitter that makes humans feel happy, calm and relaxed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Durians also have a high amount of potassium and are beneficial for blood circulation, so it is a good choice for people who have high blood pressure levels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition, durians have beneficial antioxidants and phytochemicals, for instance, carotenoid, anthocyanin, polyphenol and flavonoid, which possess the ability to reduce cholesterol, prevent atherosclerosis and reduce the risk of heart-related diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><img alt=\"Durians have several benefits to health. Photo illustration by Freepik\" src=\"https://i1-english.vnecdn.net/2023/08/20/golden-yellow-durian-flesh-sea-6681-4366-1692546612.jpg?w=680&amp;h=0&amp;q=100&amp;dpr=2&amp;fit=crop&amp;s=-9_FCTgQ17zahgbwCEBkLw\"></td></tr><tr><td>Durians have several benefits to health. Photo illustration by Freepik</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>100 grams of durian provide eaters 24% of the daily amount of vitamin C, which enhances the immune system and improves leukocyte activities. Vitamin C also helps produce more collagen, which is beneficial for the skin, hair, and nails.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, the fruit is rich in nutrients as well, and 100 grams of durian contain 147 calories. Hence, a durian pulp, which is 250 grams on average, provides around 367 calories.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of this, a person of normal conditions should not have more than four durian pulps a day. A consumption higher than this amount may cause bloating, constipation, or dyspepsia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People with diabetes should only have one to two durian pulps at a time. People with kidney failure, or who are using artificial kidneys, should also not eat durian.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is also advised not to have durian with wine, as the combination may lead to headaches, nausea, vomiting, and other undesirable effects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'What should you keep in mind when eating durian?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-should-you-keep-in-mind-when-eating-durian', '', '', '2023-08-30 08:41:28', '2023-08-30 08:41:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/trang/?p=22', 0, 'post', '', 0),
